Senator Kola Balogun, lawmaker representing Oyo South Senatorial District in the national assembly is set to join the All Progressives Congress (APC), Daily Independent has gathered. Balogun, the younger brother of the Olubadan of Ibadan, Oba Lekan Balogun earlier announced his resignation as a member of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP). The Vice-Chairman of the Senate Committee on Sports and Youth Development’s resignation came a few days after he was denied a return ticket to the Senate by PDP leaders in Oyo State led by Governor Seyi Makinde.